1
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:05,600
Unbelievable.
You remembered to take the PlayStation.

2
00:00:05,680 --> 00:00:06,880
But you forgot to turn off the water heater.

3
00:00:06,960 --> 00:00:09,680
You definitely told me to turn off the water heater.
-What water? What are you talking about?

4
00:00:09,800 --> 00:00:11,600
I didn’t shower. Why would I say something like that?

5
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:13,080
How should I know? You said it, I did it.

6
00:00:13,160 --> 00:00:16,920
And you didn’t smell the cake burning?
-No, I thought that was how it was supposed to smell.

7
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,320
Maybe at your mom's, that’s how the cake smells.

8
00:00:18,880 --> 00:00:21,400
Sit down...
Great, now I don’t have a cake either.

9
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:22,480
I didn’t even wash my hair. Are you happy?

10
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:24,760
Your hair looks just fine.
-Maybe at your mom's.

11
00:00:24,840 --> 00:00:26,680
Hair looks just fine like this.
-Sit down...

12
00:00:26,760 --> 00:00:28,880
Do me a favor, leave me alone, don’t talk to me.
-No problem.

13
00:00:33,440 --> 00:00:36,120
Look at me, look at me and...

14
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:46,480
Butterfly on the left.

15
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:51,760
What is this? What kind of thing is this?
I don’t understand how this is happening to me.

16
00:00:53,680 --> 00:00:57,000
Me? I really don’t get it.

17
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:58,040
Butterfly, butterfly.

18
00:01:01,880 --> 00:01:04,680
Mom, mom, what’s wrong? Are you okay? Drink some water.

19
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:08,960
Girls, run to the cousins
on the balcony to play. Come on, come on.

20
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:16,240
I won’t let anyone talk to me like that at home.

21
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:17,880
Of course, of course.
-I’m not okay with it.

22
00:01:17,960 --> 00:01:22,080
This is ridiculous.
If I’m living in a movie, then it’s a horror film.

23
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:24,640
I’m telling you.
-But I don’t understand. How did this happen?

24
00:01:24,720 --> 00:01:26,040
Where do I start?
-From the beginning.

25
00:01:26,640 --> 00:01:27,800
Okay, so the beginning is like this,

26
00:01:27,880 --> 00:01:31,520
It was a Wednesday,
the day the butcher's delivery guy comes,

27
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:36,000
and I had nothing left at home, no chicken breast
no ground meat, no liver,

28
00:01:36,080 --> 00:01:39,280
I wanted to make a stew so I ordered hearts too.

29
00:01:39,360 --> 00:01:43,000
And for that, you need to call him
a week in advance and pray that his cross-eyed son

30
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,960
doesn’t come because you don’t understand a word

31
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:46,080
of what he’s saying.
-Mom, mom,

32
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:48,040
Leave it, leave it, mom.
-Yeah, yeah-

33
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:51,480
So, anyway, the cute delivery guy arrives,
the tall one, the limping one...

34
00:01:51,560 --> 00:01:53,480
Ah, Nissim, cutie...
-Yeah, the cutie.

35
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:56,400
So, anyway, that day they hung on our door,

36
00:01:56,760 --> 00:02:01,160
you know, like, on the handle,
a Toto ad and a form to fill out.

37
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:03,400
Hey, Nissim.
-Hey, what’s up?

38
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:06,280
Good. How are you?
-Just hanging in there.

39
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:08,919
It was hanging on your door.
-What, is it Lotto?

40
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,840
It’s Toto. The prize is big this week.
-Come on, really, what nonsense.

41
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:15,760
Sali, what? A few million can’t hurt.

42
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:18,480
Fine.
-Give me, give me, give me, Nissim.

43
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:21,080
I’ll take it. Thanks.
-Bye, have a good day.

44
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:22,200
Come, take a look.

45
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:25,680
And then the cute Moshe arrives.
I always place an order for them

46
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:29,520
because you know how much
half a kilo of ground meat costs at their butcher.

47
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:32,640
Hello, Rachel.
-Hi, Moshe.

48
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:38,680
This is for them. Just saw them and thought of you.

49
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:41,400
Here you go.
-How nice.

50
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:45,680
You’re such a gentleman. I always tell Orna

51
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:49,560
she doesn’t know how lucky she is.
-The luck is all mine.

52
00:02:49,640 --> 00:02:54,040
You came just in time. The bourekas are warm in the oven.

53
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:56,640
Come, come, come eat something small, come.

54
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,080
Hey, Silvan-

55
00:02:58,160 --> 00:02:59,200
Move along, move along.
-Yeah.

56
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:01,480
The smell of the bourekas is killing me.

57
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:06,160
Do you want radish salad? I made it just for you.

58
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:09,080
I love radishes.
-Tell me, Moshe, what do you know

59
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:13,640
about this fruit, feijoa? The greengrocer tried
to convince me over the phone to buy some.

60
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,160
Is it the one you eat from the outside or the one with the spoon?

61
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:18,160
Good morning.
-Good morning.

62
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,560
What’s this, a break fast?

63
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:24,400
Moshe popped by to grab his meat.
-And his fridge contents.

64
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:26,400
As if I don’t know he’s here for me.

65
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:33,920
What’s up with her?
-Look, on Wednesdays she’s used to

66
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:37,680
getting the first pick. She. The girl?
-Oh!

67
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,960
What are you doing?
-Eat, eat nicely.

68
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:42,600
Sorry, I didn’t know you were here.
You’re usually in the armchair.

69
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:46,600
I have a master’s in mirbology
!a PhD in silvabology.

70
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:49,240
Why don’t you ask me
if I want you to sit on me?

71
00:03:50,320 --> 00:03:54,680
Maybe I don’t want to? I just
wanted five minutes to rest my head here,

72
00:03:54,760 --> 00:04:00,200
to relax. Not to sleep, to relax. Again.

73
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,600
I know I need to make them
think about something else.

74
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:05,520
Otherwise they just sit, get annoyed, and sulk.

75
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:09,040
Meirav, can I get you to help me fill out a lotto?

76
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:11,440
Toto.
-What’s Toto?

77
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:16,560
They put this form on my door,
and I thought it was a sign from above.

78
00:04:16,640 --> 00:04:19,279
Marked for you and all the tenants? Cool.

79
00:04:19,839 --> 00:04:22,440
What do you both even know about soccer, huh?

80
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:27,280
Meirav, it’s the big prize this week.
I have a good feeling.

81
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:30,400
Like you had a good feeling about every
guy I dated that he was the one?

82
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:33,240
No, come on, Meirav,
what we mean to say is that...

83
00:04:33,800 --> 00:04:36,480
you, you, you are special,

84
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:39,800
you’re a taste in acquisition, like

85
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:41,080
like a feijoa.

86
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:43,440
Feijoa?
-Exactly.

87
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:47,480
Exactly, feijoa. What’s a feijoa?

88
00:04:47,560 --> 00:04:49,560
Is it that, the star shape?

89
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,800
Or is it the... like a banana but...

90
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,600
straight?

91
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:58,640
Meirav, are you coming to help me fill out?
-Who even understands soccer?

92
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:01,280
I do.
-Okay.

93
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:05,640
Beitar Jerusalem, Maccabi Tel Aviv?
-One.

94
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,840
One.
-Yeah.

95
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:09,920
Beitar Jerusalem, Maccabi Tel Aviv?
-One.

96
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,320
One.

97
00:05:11,960 --> 00:05:13,640
Yeah.
-Blackpool against West Ham?

98
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:17,000
What, aren’t these just games from Israel?
-Okay, I’ll put down two.

99
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:19,200
Two is great, two is very good.
-Show me that.

100
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:22,320
Alright.
-Mönchengladbach...

101
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,240
Gladbach.

102
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:27,080
Mönchengladbach against Kaiserslautern?
-Come on, whatever.

103
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:28,880
Now I’m doing it blind, whatever happens.

104
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:32,080
Blind, so fill out the lotto.
-Come on, enough.

105
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:35,200
One, X, two, two,

106
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:36,560
X.
-Why?

107
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:37,800
Feeling.

108
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:40,120
X.
-Write down Beşiktaş.

109
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:42,400
-What? One.

110
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:45,080
X.
-Okay, enough, that’s it. Done.

111
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:48,200
I have a good feeling.
-So let’s send it.

112
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:51,520
It was so delicious, Rachel. Oh, did you fill out a Toto form?

113
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:54,920
This week’s the big prize.
-Yeah. Suddenly I felt like it.

114
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:59,040
She has a feeling.
-It’s so nice that you still have feelings, Rachel.

115
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:01,800
Moshe, how are you?
-Good.

116
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,040
Do you want me to put this
in the booth? I’m going down anyway.

117
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:07,880
Oh, yeah, yeah. That’s a good idea.
Here, I’ll give you money—

118
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:10,320
No, forget it, forget it.
-No, no, it’s fine, it’s fine.

119
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:13,440
I’ve got some change here
that wants to get rid of me. Take it.

120
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:18,440
Okay. So thanks for everything, Rachel.
-The meat goes straight to the fridge. Run, run.

121
00:06:18,520 --> 00:06:19,520
Okay, bye.
-You go.

122
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,240
Bye, Silvan.
-Move it, move it.

123
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:22,560
Love you more.
-Bye.

124
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:25,280
Ben! Ben!
-Meirav, do you want something to eat?

125
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:27,880
What does it even mean that I'm like pajamas?

126
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:30,840
That no one knows how to handle you.

127
00:06:32,920 --> 00:06:36,640
Now they're claiming it's them.
-That's not fair.

128
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:40,280
Meirav, come on, fine. Just tell me what happened.

129
00:06:40,360 --> 00:06:44,960
If it's justified, I'll help you get offended.
-Everyone knows Wednesday

130
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:47,000
is my lucky day.

131
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:50,680
Good evening.
-Finally, you got up.

132
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:52,880
Isn't it time to do something with your life?

133
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,120
I'm only here for the meat.

134
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:57,840
Really, Moshe, everyone knows you're here because of me.

135
00:06:57,960 --> 00:07:00,880
It's like it's obvious Moshe has a thing for me. It's transparent.

136
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:04,560
Maybe you should stop talking nonsense and go,
find something to do with your life.

137
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:07,320
So I decided to take a nap in the living room.

138
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:14,320
What, are you crazy?
You're really nuts, sitting on me.

139
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:18,280
Sorry, I didn't see you were here.

140
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:23,600
Tell me, isn't it enough that you live
in my house, you also want to live on me?

141
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:27,760
I'm sorry, I... look, nothing happened.

142
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:31,480
What... I'll go rest somewhere else.
-Rest somewhere...

143
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:36,640
Rest? You, rest? From what? From what to rest?

144
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:42,240
From what? Resting from work? From your husband? From your kids?

145
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:47,040
Resting. From what? From making my life hell, that's what.

146
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:50,640
Well, I have a feeling you're a bit cranky today.
-Oh, really?

147
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:54,240
So I'll go somewhere else. What's this, a lotto form?

148
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:59,240
What a coincidence, exactly today, on my lucky day.

149
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:02,080
Bad luck.

150
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:05,120
You're not filling out that garbage.
-Why not?

151
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:08,840
Because you don't understand anything about soccer, that's why not.

152
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:12,240
I have basic concepts down.

153
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:15,760
She understands soccer like she understands men.

154
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:18,520
She understands men
like I understand nuclear physics.

155
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:23,240
And I understand global economics.
-You guys are lucky it's Wednesday.

156
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:27,640
So I'm calm. Tell me! What
do you want, I'll fill out the form.

157
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:32,240
Come on, Bnei Yehuda, Bnei Sakhnin.
-Write it down.

158
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:34,679
One.
-Why?

159
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,080
Because that's how I feel.

160
00:08:36,159 --> 00:08:40,679
Give her a break, please, give her a break. Yeah.
-Beitar Jerusalem, Maccabi Tel Aviv?

161
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:49,080
One. Blackpool against West Ham?
-Write down two.

162
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:52,920
Two. Mönchengladbach against Kaiserslautern?

163
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:55,360
Okay, now you're making things up.
-No, look.

164
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:57,160
No, it's real, it's from the Bundesliga.

165
00:08:57,240 --> 00:09:00,360
So put an X.
-X.

166
00:09:01,920 --> 00:09:04,680
That's it, from now on I'm filling out for life and death.

167
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:09,600
X, one, one, two, X,

168
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:13,520
One, X.
-Who fills out a lotto like this?

169
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:17,280
Someone who has no life, that's who.
-Okay, I'm done with you guys.

170
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:18,640
We need to send this.

171
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:22,720
No, why are you looking at me
like I'm a piggy bank?

172
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:27,280
Forget it.
-I don't need you.

173
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:32,200
Moshe! Moshe!

174
00:09:32,680 --> 00:09:36,160
Now they have the nerve to say they're partners.

175
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:39,400
Wait, is that why soccer is on TV?
-Of course,

176
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:43,680
and friends, not a word to Orna about the story
and that Moshe is a pain in my ass.

177
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:46,120
Sure, sure.
-So let me tell you what happened.

178
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:50,600
I was lying there in the living room, I was resting.

179
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:55,280
Resting, not sleeping, resting.

180
00:09:58,480 --> 00:10:03,840
Rachel! Someone's at the door, interrupting my rest.

181
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:07,360
Can't you open it yourself?
-I can, but I don't want to.

182
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:09,480
Yeah, I swear.

183
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:14,320
Hey, Nissim, hey. What's up?

184
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:16,400
What's up?
-I'm good. How about you? How's your leg?

185
00:10:16,560 --> 00:10:18,840
It's heavy. They put the Toto on the door.

186
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:22,960
What, is this the form? Rachel, bring me
the form. I haven't filled one out in ages.

187
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:27,200
What, can't you take it yourself?
-I can, but I don't want to.

188
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:31,720
Yeah, I swear
No, no, let me, let me.

189
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:34,440
Thanks, thanks, Nissim.
-Bye, have a good day.

190
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:45,680
Rachel, the door! It's turning into a bus station here.

191
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:47,880
They're interrupting my rest.

192
00:10:50,640 --> 00:10:53,040
Hey, Rachel.
-Hi, Moshe.

193
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:58,040
Hey, Silvan. It's me, Moshe.
-What do you say? Is that you, Moshe?

194
00:10:58,240 --> 00:11:02,120
Wow, how nice, how did you know?
I knew because I'm Moshe.

195
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:06,320
I brought you flowers.
-How lovely.

196
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:10,040
Wait, wait. Where did these flowers come from?
-I found them downstairs,

197
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:12,920
someone threw them out, they're brand new.
They just need a little water.

198
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:16,720
Rachel, throw those flowers away,
you don't know who touched them first.

199
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:20,480
It doesn't matter, Moshe. It's the thought that counts.

200
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:24,160
What thought?
-It doesn't matter, Moshe.

201
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:25,080
What?

202
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:26,640
Want to eat?
-Are there radishes?

203
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:30,480
Yes, come.
-Rachel, the form. Rachel, the form!

204
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:31,720
Just a second.

205
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,560
It's the week of the big prize.

206
00:11:39,760 --> 00:11:42,880
I thought I'd buy a little boat,

207
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,440
we'll sail on the Kinneret.

208
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:50,200
We'll catch fish, I really love nature.

209
00:11:50,280 --> 00:11:51,200
What, you can see.

210
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:53,320
Yeah
Come on

211
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:55,920
No, but okay, I get that you’re a bit overwhelmed.

212
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:00,560
And then, then the problems started,

213
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:04,680
serious problems.

214
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:07,120
Oh!

215
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:11,000
Bubala, bubala, what happened to you?

216
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:13,960
What, you almost sat down...
-By mistake! What's wrong with you?

217
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:20,240
No, bubala, my little bird.
Dad just wanted to rest a bit, that's all.

218
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:22,840
I can't, Dad.
-I, I

219
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:26,600
Moshe keeps trying to hit on me.
-Moshe?

220
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:30,600
Moshe is nothing. You should see
how Shai looks at me all the time.

221
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:34,960
Stop the story.
Meirav said I'm trying to hit on her?

222
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:37,200
And that's just the sane part.

223
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:40,680
Are you sure?
-Of course I'm sure. It's stronger than them.

224
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:43,480
They can't control themselves.
They're waiting for me by the bathtub,

225
00:12:43,560 --> 00:12:46,480
by the bathroom...
-Of course, of course, of course.

